criteria.driver_alignment:
Discover — identified and applied the firm's 8.5% WACC as the hurdle rate;  
Validate — checked cash‑flow patterns and discounting logic (internal validation);  
Evolve — ran sensitivity tests (revenue down 20%, WACC ±2%) to test assumptions.

DISCOVER — identified the 8.5% WACC hurdle and NPV/IRR/payback decision rules; 
REPRESENT — laid out the year‑0 to 10 cash‑flow construction (revenues, COGS, depreciation, taxes, WC, terminal value) and discounting approach; 
IMPLEMENT — coded and calculated NPV, IRR, paybacks, and PI; 
EVOLVE — ran sensitivity tests (revenue shortfall and WACC variations); 
REFLECT — tied quantitative results and sensitivities to a clear recommendation.
